org.gvsig.fmap.dal.coverage.store.parameter

Interface NewRasterStoreParameters

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataParameters, DataStoreParameters, DynObject, NewDataStoreParameters, Persistent
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNewRasterStoreParameters, ErmapperNewRasterStoreParameters, GdalNewRasterStoreParameters, TileFileFormatNewRasterStoreParameters

    public interface NewRasterStoreParameters
extends NewDataStoreParameters
    This class represents parameters that we need to create a new raster source.

      • setBand

        void setBand(int n)
        Sets the number of band in the buffer that will be saved. If this value is greater than zero only one band (n) will be written. If this value is lower than zero then all bands will be written. This is the value by default.
        Parameters:
        n -

      • setAffineTransform

        void setAffineTransform(AffineTransform at)
        Deprecated. 
        This method is maintained to keep compatibility with the old system. It is recommended not to use. If the buffer don't have bounding box the affine transform will be the identity and if not the affine transform will be calculated using the geographic information.
        Parameters:
        at -

      • getAffineTransform

        AffineTransform getAffineTransform()
        This method is maintained to keep compatibility with the old system. It is recommended not to use. If the buffer don't have bounding box the affine transform will be the identity and if not the affine transform will be calculated using the geographic information.
